cs.IT, cs.SP, cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.MM 

The paper discusses an algorithm for signal reconstruction in compressive sensing, which involves linear measurement operators and sparse signals. This falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP). The paper also mentions modifications to the algorithm that involve least squares and polynomial acceleration, which are techniques used in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). The adaptive method for choosing the step-length is a machine learning technique, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents empirical evidence for the effectiveness of the modified algorithms, which could be considered as a Multimedia (cs.MM) application.
